Photo by @FransLanting. The magic light of dawn adds a serene mood to a scenic beach near Santa Cruz, where fresh water from a local creek flows into the salt water of the Monterey Bay at a tideline where rocks eroded from a coastal cliff add a touch of permanence to an otherwise fluid scene. This is one of my favorite places to teach photographers during our workshops how you can create dynamic landscape photos by allowing nature’s serendipity to interact with your own creative vision. If you’re interested to join us for a future session, please sign up for our mailing list by writing to info@lanting.com. Stay tuned for more images from our workshops along the Central Coast of California. 
